  <tr>
   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>In mysite/base/templates/base/base.html there is the following line:

&lt;script type='text/javascript'
src='<a href="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.7.2/jquery.min.js">https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.7.2/jquery.min.js</a>'&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

It turns out that indeed, we are already including a version of jQuery from
beyond the stone age. 

A possible follow-up to this issue would be to go through the code and remove
unused, outdated jQuery within the repo.</pre>
   </td>
  </tr>
 
 
  <tr>
   <th><a href="msg4390">msg4390 (view)</a></th>
